It's an intense rhythm, but the villagers' musicians generally help the team stay motivated.
"They hit drummers all night to keep us awake so that we can continue to work," Bwelle explained.
On Sunday, the team returns to the city, tired but proud of the work she has done.
The group, composed of Cameroonian physicians and medical students, performed 700 surgical acts free of charge in the past year, and he knows that their presence can make all the difference for those to whom they help.
